{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P7aY1NqzxMSadEkgdcL6kh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package web\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"context\"\n     5→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6→\t\"fmt\"\n     7→\t\"net/http\"\n     8→\t\"net/http/httptest\"\n     9→\t\"os\"\n    10→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    11→\t\"strings\"\n    12→\t\"testing\"\n    13→\t\"time\"\n    14→\n    15→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/sqlite\"\n    16→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    17→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    18→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n    19→\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/require\"\n    20→)\n    21→\n    22→// mockContainerManager implements ContainerManager for testing.\n    23→type mockContainerManager struct {\n    24→\tcontainers map[string]bool // containerID -> exists\n    25→\trunning    map[string]bool // containerID -> running\n    26→\tremoved    []string\n    27→\tstopped    []string\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→func newMockContainerManager() *mockContainerManager {\n    31→\treturn &mockContainerManager{\n    32→\t\tcontainers: map[string]bool{},\n    33→\t\trunning:    map[string]bool{},\n    34→\t}\n    35→}\n    36→\n    37→func (m *mockContainerManager) Logs(_ context.Context, containerID string) (string, error) {\n    38→\treturn \"mock logs\", nil\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→func (m *mockContainerManager) Stop(_ context.Context, containerID string) error {\n    42→\tif !m.containers[containerID] {\n    43→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"container %s not found\", containerID)\n    44→\t}\n    45→\tm.running[containerID] = false\n    46→\tm.stopped = append(m.stopped, containerID)\n    47→\treturn nil\n    48→}\n    49→\n    50→func (m *mockContainerManager) Remove(_ context.Context, containerID string) error {\n    51→\tif !m.containers[containerID] {\n    52→\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"container %s not found\", containerID)\n    53→\t}\n    54→\tdelete(m.containers, containerID)\n    55→\tm.removed = append(m.removed, containerID)\n    56→\treturn nil\n    57→}\n    58→\n    59→func (m *mockContainerManager) Inspect(_ context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error) {\n    60→\tif !m.containers[containerID] {\n    61→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"container %s not found\", containerID)\n    62→\t}\n    63→\treturn &ports.ContainerStatus{Running: m.running[containerID], ExitCode: 0}, nil\n    64→}\n    65→\n    66→func setupHandler(t *testing.T) (*Handler, *sqlite.Store) {\n    67→\tt.Helper()\n    68→\tstore, err := sqlite.NewStore(\":memory:\")\n    69→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    70→\tt.Cleanup(func() { store.Close() })\n    71→\n    72→\th, err := NewHandler(store, store)\n    73→\trequire.NoError(t, err)\n    74→\treturn h, store\n    75→}\n    76→\n    77→func seedRun(t *testing.T, store *sqlite.Store, id, workflow string, state domain.RunState) {\n    78→\tt.Helper()\n    79→\tseedRunWithProject(t, store, id, workflow, state, \"\")\n    80→}\n    81→\n    82→func seedRunWithProject(t *testing.T, store *sqlite.Store, id, workflow string, state domain.RunState, projectDir string) {\n    83→\tt.Helper()\n    84→\tctx := context.Background()\n    85→\trun := domain.NewRun(id, workflow)\n    86→\trun.ProjectDir = projectDir\n    87→\tif state != domain.RunStatePending {\n    88→\t\trun.Start()\n    89→\t\trun.ContainerID = \"abc123def456789\"\n    90→\t}\n    91→\tif state == domain.RunStateSucceeded || state == domain.RunStateFailed {\n    92→\t\trun.Complete(state)\n    93→\t}\n    94→\tif state == domain.RunStateFailed {\n    95→\t\trun.ErrorMessage = \"something went wrong\"\n    96→\t}\n    97→\trequire.NoError(t, store.CreateRun(ctx, run))\n    98→}\n    99→\n   100→func TestRunsList_WithRuns(t *testing.T) {"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013XQfDqEQmSNKz8rGm66953","session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","uuid":"b6017396-f436-4be5-9296-b46cced5ccbf"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_notification","task_id":"a80bb21dba5754073","tool_use_id":"toolu_013XQfDqEQmSNKz8rGm66953","status":"completed","output_file":"","summary":"Explore log serving architecture","usage":{"total_tokens":65852,"tool_uses":41,"duration_ms":73317},"uuid":"50ab5088-ffa9-4224-a1bf-e7eed36941cd","session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013XQfDqEQmSNKz8rGm66953","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create the final report.\n\n## Summary: Log Serving Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of how logs are served in this project. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. CLI `cloche logs` Command Path\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 250-396)\n\nThe CLI has two modes:\n\n### Non-Follow Mode (`cloche logs <run-id>`)\n- Uses **gRPC** to connect to the daemon (line 283)\n- Calls `client.StreamLogs()` with optional filters (step name, log type)\n- Receives `pb.LogEntry` messages and formats them for terminal display\n- Handles multiple entry types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `full_log`, `log`, and filtered types like `script_log`/`llm_log`\n\n### Follow Mode (`cloche logs <run-id> --follow`)\n- Uses **HTTP SSE (Server-Sent Events)** instead of gRPC (lines 336-396)\n- Connects to `http://{CLOCHE_HTTP}/api/runs/{runID}/stream` (line 345)\n- Parses SSE events with `data: {JSON}` format\n- Color-codes output by type (status=blue, llm=green, etc.)\n\n**Critical difference:** Follow mode reads from a different endpoint than normal mode, which could cause inconsistencies.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Web UI Log Serving\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### Endpoints:\n\n1. **`GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`** - SSE Stream (lines 805-871)\n   - For **completed runs**: Reads archived `full.log` file from disk and streams it (lines 833-838)\n   - For **active runs**: Subscribes to live broadcaster (lines 841-870)\n   - Falls back to `ServiceUnavailable` if no broadcaster configured\n\n2. **`GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`** - Step Output (lines 583-658)\n   - Uses log index first via `LogStore` (lines 604-618)\n   - Falls back to file path conventions: `{step}.log`, then `container.log`\n   - Last resort: queries live container logs via `ContainerLogger` (lines 650-654)\n\n### Helper Functions:\n- `streamFullLog()` - Reads `full.log` line-by-line and parses format `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` - Converts Claude JSON to human-readable text\n- `parseFullLogLine()` - Regex-based parser for structured log lines\n\n---\n\n## 3. Log Storage & CaptureStore Architecture\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\nThree separate interfaces handle logs:\n\n### `CaptureStore` interface\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx, runID, exec *StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx, runID) ([]*StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n- Stores step execution metadata (step name, result, timing)\n- Used during run to track progress\n- Falls back when full.log is missing (gRPC server line 510-551)\n\n### `LogStore` interface (NEW)\n```go\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx, runID) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx, runID, fileType) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n- Indexes extracted log files in SQLite (fields: `run_id`, `step_name`, `file_type`, `file_path`, `file_size`, `created_at`)\n- File types: `\"full\"`, `\"script\"`, `\"llm\"`\n- Step name only populated for script/llm logs, empty for full.log\n\n---\n\n## 4. Log File Indexing & Extraction Flow\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 819-872)\n\nAfter container completes, the daemon:\n\n1. **Extracts output files** to `.cloche/{run-id}/output/` (line 286-293)\n   - `full.log` - Complete unified log\n   - `{stepName}.log` - Per-step script output\n   - `llm-{stepName}.log` - LLM-specific output\n   - `container.log` - Raw Docker container logs\n\n2. **Indexes log files** in SQLite via `s.indexLogFiles()` (line 300)\n   - Scans output directory for `.log` files\n   - Classifies by filename pattern\n   - Skips `container.log` (internal only)\n   - Inserts into `log_files` table with timestamp and size\n\n3. **Note:** Indexing happens **AFTER** state finalization (line 343)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Live Log Broadcasting\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n\nIn-memory broadcaster for active runs:\n\n```go\ntype Broadcaster struct {\n    mu   sync.Mutex\n    runs map[string]*runBroadcast\n}\n```\n\n- **Publish()** - Non-blocking send to subscriber channels (drops if buffer full, line 107)\n- **Subscribe()** - Returns buffered channel (256 capacity, line 64)\n- **Finish()** - Marks run complete, closes all subscriber channels\n- **Thread-safe** - All operations protected by mutex\n\nThe broadcaster is instantiated in daemon and shared with:\n- gRPC server (`SetLogBroadcaster()`, line 75)\n- Web handler (`WithLogBroadcaster()`, web/handler.go line 42)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Potential Issues: Web UI vs CLI Log Inconsistencies\n\n### Issue 1: Different Log Serving Paths\n\n**CLI Follow Mode** → HTTP SSE → `web/handler.go:handleAPIStream()`\n- Reads `full.log` from disk\n- Streams live broadcaster for active runs\n\n**CLI Normal Mode** → gRPC → `grpc/server.go:StreamLogs()`\n- Reads broadcaster for active runs\n- Falls back to `full.log`, then to CaptureStore+file lookups\n\n**Web UI** → HTTP SSE → Same endpoint as CLI follow mode\n- BUT: No caching between them; both read from broadcaster/disk\n\n### Issue 2: Race Condition on Run Completion\n\nIn `grpc/server.go`:\n\n```go\n// Line 298-300: Index logs AFTER container completes\nif s.logStore != nil {\n    s.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n}\n// Line 328-343: THEN update run state\nrun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n```\n\n**Problem:** There's a small window where:\n1. Container exits\n2. Output files extracted\n3. Broadcaster publishes completion to SSE subscribers\n4. Logs not yet indexed in database\n5. Web UI queries log index and gets \"not found\"\n\n### Issue 3: Broadcaster State Lost on Daemon Restart\n\nThe broadcaster is in-memory only. If daemon crashes while a run is \"running\":\n- SSE clients get `ServiceUnavailable` (web/handler.go line 843)\n- `cloche logs --follow` fails to connect\n- But gRPC can still serve from files if `full.log` exists\n\n### Issue 4: activeRun Detection Bug (Potential)\n\nIn `web/handler.go:handleAPIStream()` lines 828-839:\n\n```go\nisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n    run.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n    run.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n\nif isComplete {\n    h.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run) // Read from disk\n    return\n}\n```\n\nBut in `grpc/server.go:StreamLogs()` lines 479-481:\n\n```go\nif (run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending) && \n   s.logBroadcast != nil {\n    return s.streamLiveLogs(req.RunId, stream)\n}\n```\n\n**Race condition:** If run completes between web handler check and broadcaster subscription, different code paths execute. Web serves `full.log`, gRPC tries broadcaster (now finished, returns nil channel).\n\n### Issue 5: Log Index Not Populated for Old Runs\n\nThe `log_files` table is only populated at extraction time (line 868). Existing runs completed before this feature was added have no index entries. The fallback to file paths still works, but the index optimization is skipped.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Files\n\n**Log Storage & Indexing:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - LogStore implementation (lines 307-348)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Port definitions\n\n**CLI:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - `cmdLogs()` and `cmdLogsFollow()`\n\n**gRPC Server:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - `StreamLogs()`, `streamLiveLogs()`, `streamFilteredLogs()`, `indexLogFiles()`\n\n**Web Handler:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - `handleAPIStream()`, `handleAPIStepOutput()`, `streamFullLog()`\n\n**Broadcasting:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - In-memory pub/sub\n\n**Tests:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - SSE stream tests\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Web handler tests\n\n---\n\n## 8. Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ ACTIVE RUN                                                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Container output → Agent writes logs → gRPC publishes to        │\n│ Broadcaster (in-memory queue)                                   │\n│                                                                 │\n│ CLI (follow):       → HTTP SSE → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓     │\n│ Web UI (stream):    → HTTP SSE → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓     │\n│ gRPC StreamLogs():  → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ COMPLETED RUN                                                   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ 1. Output extracted to: .cloche/{runID}/output/                 │\n│ 2. Log files indexed in SQLite log_files table                  │\n│ 3. Run state updated to succeeded/failed                        │\n│                                                                 │\n│ CLI (normal):       → gRPC → Check full.log → Falls back to    │\n│                      CaptureStore + per-step files ✓            │\n│ CLI (follow):       → HTTP SSE → Read full.log directly ✓       │\n│ Web UI (stream):    → HTTP SSE → Read full.log directly ✓       │\n│ Web UI (step out):  → HTTP GET → Log index → Fallback to       │\n│                      file paths ✓                               │\n│ gRPC (filtered):    → Check log index → Fallback to file        │\n│                      paths ✓                                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a80bb21dba5754073 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68472\ntool_uses: 41\nduration_ms: 73323</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","uuid":"576498d3-70ee-4820-a2a2-921fe2c6d1e5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore how logs are served in this project. I need to understand:\n1. How the CLI `cloche logs` command works\n2. How the Web UI serves logs\n3. How logs are stored and retrieved (the CaptureStore / log store)\n4. Any differences between the two paths that could cause the web UI to show wrong/stale log data\n\nLook at:\n- cmd/cloche/ for CLI log commands\n- Any web/HTTP server code\n- internal/ports/ for CaptureStore interface\n- internal/adapters/ for log storage implementations\n- Any API endpoints that serve logs\n\nBe very thorough - search for \"log\", \"capture\", \"web\", \"http\", \"handler\", \"serve\" patterns.","agentId":"a80bb21dba5754073","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive information. Let me create the final report.\n\n## Summary: Log Serving Architecture in Cloche\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of how logs are served in this project. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. CLI `cloche logs` Command Path\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 250-396)\n\nThe CLI has two modes:\n\n### Non-Follow Mode (`cloche logs <run-id>`)\n- Uses **gRPC** to connect to the daemon (line 283)\n- Calls `client.StreamLogs()` with optional filters (step name, log type)\n- Receives `pb.LogEntry` messages and formats them for terminal display\n- Handles multiple entry types: `step_started`, `step_completed`, `run_completed`, `full_log`, `log`, and filtered types like `script_log`/`llm_log`\n\n### Follow Mode (`cloche logs <run-id> --follow`)\n- Uses **HTTP SSE (Server-Sent Events)** instead of gRPC (lines 336-396)\n- Connects to `http://{CLOCHE_HTTP}/api/runs/{runID}/stream` (line 345)\n- Parses SSE events with `data: {JSON}` format\n- Color-codes output by type (status=blue, llm=green, etc.)\n\n**Critical difference:** Follow mode reads from a different endpoint than normal mode, which could cause inconsistencies.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Web UI Log Serving\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n### Endpoints:\n\n1. **`GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`** - SSE Stream (lines 805-871)\n   - For **completed runs**: Reads archived `full.log` file from disk and streams it (lines 833-838)\n   - For **active runs**: Subscribes to live broadcaster (lines 841-870)\n   - Falls back to `ServiceUnavailable` if no broadcaster configured\n\n2. **`GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`** - Step Output (lines 583-658)\n   - Uses log index first via `LogStore` (lines 604-618)\n   - Falls back to file path conventions: `{step}.log`, then `container.log`\n   - Last resort: queries live container logs via `ContainerLogger` (lines 650-654)\n\n### Helper Functions:\n- `streamFullLog()` - Reads `full.log` line-by-line and parses format `[timestamp] [type] content`\n- `parseLLMLogLine()` - Converts Claude JSON to human-readable text\n- `parseFullLogLine()` - Regex-based parser for structured log lines\n\n---\n\n## 3. Log Storage & CaptureStore Architecture\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`\n\nThree separate interfaces handle logs:\n\n### `CaptureStore` interface\n```go\ntype CaptureStore interface {\n    SaveCapture(ctx, runID, exec *StepExecution) error\n    GetCaptures(ctx, runID) ([]*StepExecution, error)\n}\n```\n- Stores step execution metadata (step name, result, timing)\n- Used during run to track progress\n- Falls back when full.log is missing (gRPC server line 510-551)\n\n### `LogStore` interface (NEW)\n```go\ntype LogStore interface {\n    SaveLogFile(ctx, entry *LogFileEntry) error\n    GetLogFiles(ctx, runID) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFilesByStep(ctx, runID, stepName) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n    GetLogFileByType(ctx, runID, fileType) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n}\n```\n- Indexes extracted log files in SQLite (fields: `run_id`, `step_name`, `file_type`, `file_path`, `file_size`, `created_at`)\n- File types: `\"full\"`, `\"script\"`, `\"llm\"`\n- Step name only populated for script/llm logs, empty for full.log\n\n---\n\n## 4. Log File Indexing & Extraction Flow\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 819-872)\n\nAfter container completes, the daemon:\n\n1. **Extracts output files** to `.cloche/{run-id}/output/` (line 286-293)\n   - `full.log` - Complete unified log\n   - `{stepName}.log` - Per-step script output\n   - `llm-{stepName}.log` - LLM-specific output\n   - `container.log` - Raw Docker container logs\n\n2. **Indexes log files** in SQLite via `s.indexLogFiles()` (line 300)\n   - Scans output directory for `.log` files\n   - Classifies by filename pattern\n   - Skips `container.log` (internal only)\n   - Inserts into `log_files` table with timestamp and size\n\n3. **Note:** Indexing happens **AFTER** state finalization (line 343)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Live Log Broadcasting\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n\nIn-memory broadcaster for active runs:\n\n```go\ntype Broadcaster struct {\n    mu   sync.Mutex\n    runs map[string]*runBroadcast\n}\n```\n\n- **Publish()** - Non-blocking send to subscriber channels (drops if buffer full, line 107)\n- **Subscribe()** - Returns buffered channel (256 capacity, line 64)\n- **Finish()** - Marks run complete, closes all subscriber channels\n- **Thread-safe** - All operations protected by mutex\n\nThe broadcaster is instantiated in daemon and shared with:\n- gRPC server (`SetLogBroadcaster()`, line 75)\n- Web handler (`WithLogBroadcaster()`, web/handler.go line 42)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Potential Issues: Web UI vs CLI Log Inconsistencies\n\n### Issue 1: Different Log Serving Paths\n\n**CLI Follow Mode** → HTTP SSE → `web/handler.go:handleAPIStream()`\n- Reads `full.log` from disk\n- Streams live broadcaster for active runs\n\n**CLI Normal Mode** → gRPC → `grpc/server.go:StreamLogs()`\n- Reads broadcaster for active runs\n- Falls back to `full.log`, then to CaptureStore+file lookups\n\n**Web UI** → HTTP SSE → Same endpoint as CLI follow mode\n- BUT: No caching between them; both read from broadcaster/disk\n\n### Issue 2: Race Condition on Run Completion\n\nIn `grpc/server.go`:\n\n```go\n// Line 298-300: Index logs AFTER container completes\nif s.logStore != nil {\n    s.indexLogFiles(ctx, runID, outputDst)\n}\n// Line 328-343: THEN update run state\nrun.Complete(domain.RunStateSucceeded)\n_ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n```\n\n**Problem:** There's a small window where:\n1. Container exits\n2. Output files extracted\n3. Broadcaster publishes completion to SSE subscribers\n4. Logs not yet indexed in database\n5. Web UI queries log index and gets \"not found\"\n\n### Issue 3: Broadcaster State Lost on Daemon Restart\n\nThe broadcaster is in-memory only. If daemon crashes while a run is \"running\":\n- SSE clients get `ServiceUnavailable` (web/handler.go line 843)\n- `cloche logs --follow` fails to connect\n- But gRPC can still serve from files if `full.log` exists\n\n### Issue 4: activeRun Detection Bug (Potential)\n\nIn `web/handler.go:handleAPIStream()` lines 828-839:\n\n```go\nisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n    run.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n    run.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n\nif isComplete {\n    h.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run) // Read from disk\n    return\n}\n```\n\nBut in `grpc/server.go:StreamLogs()` lines 479-481:\n\n```go\nif (run.State == domain.RunStateRunning || run.State == domain.RunStatePending) && \n   s.logBroadcast != nil {\n    return s.streamLiveLogs(req.RunId, stream)\n}\n```\n\n**Race condition:** If run completes between web handler check and broadcaster subscription, different code paths execute. Web serves `full.log`, gRPC tries broadcaster (now finished, returns nil channel).\n\n### Issue 5: Log Index Not Populated for Old Runs\n\nThe `log_files` table is only populated at extraction time (line 868). Existing runs completed before this feature was added have no index entries. The fallback to file paths still works, but the index optimization is skipped.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Key Files\n\n**Log Storage & Indexing:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` - LogStore implementation (lines 307-348)\n- `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` - Port definitions\n\n**CLI:**\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - `cmdLogs()` and `cmdLogsFollow()`\n\n**gRPC Server:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - `StreamLogs()`, `streamLiveLogs()`, `streamFilteredLogs()`, `indexLogFiles()`\n\n**Web Handler:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - `handleAPIStream()`, `handleAPIStepOutput()`, `streamFullLog()`\n\n**Broadcasting:**\n- `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` - In-memory pub/sub\n\n**Tests:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - SSE stream tests\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Web handler tests\n\n---\n\n## 8. Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ ACTIVE RUN                                                      │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ Container output → Agent writes logs → gRPC publishes to        │\n│ Broadcaster (in-memory queue)                                   │\n│                                                                 │\n│ CLI (follow):       → HTTP SSE → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓     │\n│ Web UI (stream):    → HTTP SSE → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓     │\n│ gRPC StreamLogs():  → Subscribe to Broadcaster ✓                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ COMPLETED RUN                                                   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│ 1. Output extracted to: .cloche/{runID}/output/                 │\n│ 2. Log files indexed in SQLite log_files table                  │\n│ 3. Run state updated to succeeded/failed                        │\n│                                                                 │\n│ CLI (normal):       → gRPC → Check full.log → Falls back to    │\n│                      CaptureStore + per-step files ✓            │\n│ CLI (follow):       → HTTP SSE → Read full.log directly ✓       │\n│ Web UI (stream):    → HTTP SSE → Read full.log directly ✓       │\n│ Web UI (step out):  → HTTP GET → Log index → Fallback to       │\n│                      file paths ✓                               │\n│ gRPC (filtered):    → Check log index → Fallback to file        │\n│                      paths ✓                                    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```"}],"totalDurationMs":73323,"totalTokens":68472,"totalToolUseCount":41,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1527,"cache_read_input_tokens":64038,"output_tokens":2903,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1527},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
