{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JpszamhtsvQRkFUNR6L9xg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of the bug. Let me summarize:\n\n**The Bug:** In `handleAPIStepOutput` (handler.go:583-658), when a step-specific log file (e.g., `implement.log`) is not found, the code falls back to reading the entire `container.log` file and serving it as the output for that specific step. `container.log` contains ALL output from ALL steps in the container, including stdout/stderr from everything. This means the web UI can show errors or output from other steps when viewing a specific step's log.\n\nThe CLI (`cloche logs`) uses a different code path - `StreamLogs` in grpc/server.go. For the default path (no step filter), it reads `full.log` which is a unified structured log. When it falls back to captures with per-step files, it ALSO has the same `container.log` fallback bug, but the default/common CLI path uses `full.log` which doesn't have this issue.\n \nThe fix is to replace the `container.log` fallback with a smarter approach: try the step-specific log file first, then attempt to read `full.log` and filter it to only show lines for the requested step, and only as a last resort try live container logs. This removes the problematic unfiltered fallback that mixes output from all steps. line - it's inferred from `step_started` and `step_completed` status lines.\n\nLooking at how the broadcaster publishes logs, it includes the step name directly in each log line. But I need to check whether `full.log` actually captures that step information when it's parsed. Let me trace through the `parseFullLogLine` function to see what fields are being extracted from the log format.\n\nThe full.log parser only extracts timestamp, type, and content - there's no step name in that line format. So the real solution is to remove the `container.log` fallback entirely from `handleAPIStepOutput`. If a step-specific log file doesn't exist, we should return 404 instead of serving the entire container's output as a workaround. The same logic applies to the gRPC StreamLogs fallback and the live Docker logs fallback - all of these are returning too much data when they should be honest about not having step-specific output.\n\nI'm thinking through whether to keep the live logs fallback since it's useful when the run is still active and logs haven't been extracted yet, but even then it's showing all container output rather than filtering to just the step.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3982,"cache_read_input_tokens":39909,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3982},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","uuid":"00bcefd0-e3d4-4f14-86db-d5936ec8c33b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JpszamhtsvQRkFUNR6L9xg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've identified the bug. In `handleAPIStepOutput` (handler.go:642-655), when a step-specific log file is missing, the web UI falls back to serving the **entire** `container.log`, which contains raw output from ALL steps mixed together. This is why the web UI shows wrong content for a specific step — it's showing the whole container's output instead. The CLI doesn't hit this path because it uses `full.log` by default.\n\nThe same bug exists in the gRPC server's capture-based fallback (server.go:534-538).\n\nLet me fix both:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3982,"cache_read_input_tokens":39909,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3982},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","uuid":"4c2ab774-fa59-445c-8690-b29d3e817877"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JpszamhtsvQRkFUNR6L9xg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01FBVVWw5wDSHBAtBD6k5b2x","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go","old_string":"\t// Try per-step output first, fall back to container.log, then live docker logs\n\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcontainerLog := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"container.log\")\n\tdata, err = os.ReadFile(containerLog)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Last resort: try live docker logs from still-existing container\n\tif h.container != nil && run.ContainerID != \"\" {\n\t\tif logs, logErr := h.container.Logs(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n\t\t\twriteOutput([]byte(logs))\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)","new_string":"\t// Try per-step output file\n\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Do NOT fall back to container.log or live docker logs here — those\n\t// contain unfiltered output from ALL steps and would show the wrong\n\t// content for this specific step (the root cause of web-UI log mismatches).\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3982,"cache_read_input_tokens":39909,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3982},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"sessio