{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01397cd8PsfpfQP5aY4FoLzQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause:** When the web UI requested step-specific output (e.g., `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/implement/output`), and the per-step log file (`implement.log`) was missing, the handler fell back to serving the **entire** `container.log` — which contains unfiltered, mixed output from ALL steps. This caused the web UI to show content from other steps (like a \"limit reached\" error) when viewing a specific step's logs. The CLI didn't hit this path because `cloche logs` defaults to reading `full.log` as a unified stream.\n\n**Changes:**\n1. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** — Removed the `container.log` and live docker logs fallbacks from `handleAPIStepOutput`. Now returns 404 when a step-specific log file doesn't exist, rather than serving wrong content.\n2. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Removed the same `container.log` fallback from the gRPC `StreamLogs` capture-based path for consistency.\n3. **Tests updated:** Renamed `TestServer_StreamLogs_FallsBackToContainerLog` to `TestServer_StreamLogs_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog` and verified the new behavior. Added three new web handler tests (`TestStepOutput_ReturnsStepLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToLiveDockerLogs`).\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":751,"cache_read_input_tokens":58196,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":751},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","uuid":"1f3fd712-6722-4aa4-b9ee-3840523ab34d"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":295620,"duration_api_ms":256377,"num_turns":26,"result":"All tests pass. Here's a summary of the fix:\n\n**Root cause:** When the web UI requested step-specific output (e.g., `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/implement/output`), and the per-step log file (`implement.log`) was missing, the handler fell back to serving the **entire** `container.log` — which contains unfiltered, mixed output from ALL steps. This caused the web UI to show content from other steps (like a \"limit reached\" error) when viewing a specific step's logs. The CLI didn't hit this path because `cloche logs` defaults to reading `full.log` as a unified stream.\n\n**Changes:**\n1. **`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** — Removed the `container.log` and live docker logs fallbacks from `handleAPIStepOutput`. Now returns 404 when a step-specific log file doesn't exist, rather than serving wrong content.\n2. **`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`** — Removed the same `container.log` fallback from the gRPC `StreamLogs` capture-based path for consistency.\n3. **Tests updated:** Renamed `TestServer_StreamLogs_FallsBackToContainerLog` to `TestServer_StreamLogs_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog` and verified the new behavior. Added three new web handler tests (`TestStepOutput_ReturnsStepLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToContainerLog`, `TestStepOutput_DoesNotFallBackToLiveDockerLogs`).\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"ad3012fc-7915-4d91-bc2f-6e4358dcbb9c","total_cost_usd":1.1633223000000001,"usage":{"input_tokens":4774,"cache_creation_input_tokens":50297,"cache_read_input_tokens":816661,"output_tokens":9482,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":50297,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":4774,"outputTokens":9482,"cacheReadInpu